Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove} (or use a #garlic press{}). Zest the @lime{1/2%whole} and cut into wedges. Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the @rainbow chard{150%g} and fry until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add a splash of @water{} to help it wilt. Add the garlic, fry for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the @king prawns{180%g} and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the sweetcorn and @steamed coconut basmati rice{1%portion}, use a #spatula{} to break-up the rice. Cook for ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the @Pad Thai paste{50%g} and @mango chutney{40%g} until all combined and piping hot. Add the lime zest and coriander and stir through. Divide between plates and serve with the lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!